dct_title_s: Franklin Quadrangle Indiana : 15 minute series (topographic) [1950 printing with vegetation]
dct_description_sm: Filing title: Franklin, Ind. Mapped, edited, and published by Geological Survey. Edition of 1950. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Contour interval 20 feet. Includes quadrangle location map. Some copies have forest areas colored green. Reprinted 1964 without edition information. At head of map: United States, Department of the Army, Corps of Engineers. "Culture and drainage from aerial photographs by multiplex methods. Aerial photographs taken 1941 and 1944. Contours by plane-table surveys 1947." "This area also covered by 7.5 minute, 1:24000-scale maps: Franklin 1947, Trafalgar 1947, Fruitdale 1947, and Ninevah 1947." "N3915--W8600/15."
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army. Corps of Engineers
